title.narrative: Malaria Vaccine Development Program (MVDP) / National Institute of Allergy and Infectious Diseases (NIAID)

description.narrative: The purpose of the National Institute of Allergy and Infectious Diseases IAA is to develop malaria vaccines for use in control programs in the developing world. Through a cadre of partners dedicated to the malaria vaccine development enterprise, the Malaria Vaccine Development Program produces candidate vaccines and evaluates them in the laboratory, the clinic, and the field.
